I take another pass of the current c++ code. One limitation of current generic func system, which I don't like is that it relies on func_name as the key to query for both register and invoke. I hope we have a cleaner solution, which makes GenericFunc object as an interop object between python and c++. This can likely be done by making GenericFunc as a Node. 

The only thing to keep in mind is that we should avoid registering it to the Node constructor registry since it does not support serialization. Otherwise, it works like a traditional object, we can add additional member functions like

```python
@tvm.register
class GenericFunc(Node):
   def __call__(*args):
       if self._call_functor is None:
          self._call_functor = _api_internal._GenericFuncCallFunctor(self)
      self._call_functor(*args)
```

